elements.text: Gout is a common and complex form of inflammatory arthritis, resulting from the deposition of monosodium urate monohydrate crystals. With persistent urate crystal deposition, gout may progress from acute episodic attacks to a disabling chronic deforming arthropathy, with destructive deposits of urate crystals (tophi) in bones, joints, subcutaneous tissue, and other organs.
